<subSubSection pageId="108" pageNumber="387" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="108.[2071,2666,2936,3359]" pageId="108" pageNumber="387">
<taxonomicName box="[2072,2217,3050,3083]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peromyscus</taxonomicName>
salvadorensis is in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[2531,2666,3050,3083]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">mexicanus</taxonomicName>
species group. It was initially described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[2349,2524,3129,3162]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">P. mexicanus</taxonomicName>
but later placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[2483,2666,3168,3201]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">P. mexicanus</taxonomicName>
saxatilis. Recent DNA studies suggest that parts of what historically have been recognized as P. m. saxatilis should be considered as P. salvadorensis or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1908" box="[2478,2657,3326,3359]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nicaraguae">P. nicaraguae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="108.[1460,2664,3371,3478]" box="[1460,1620,3371,3400]" pageId="108" pageNumber="387">Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1460,2252,3410,3439]" pageId="108" pageNumber="387" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761038" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6761038" box="[1460,2252,3410,3439]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761038/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="387" startId="108.[1460,1632,3410,3439]" targetBox="[1457,2048,2943,3358]" targetPageId="108">
<paragraph blockId="108.[1460,2664,3371,3478]" box="[1460,2252,3410,3439]" pageId="108" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1460,1636,3410,3439]" pageId="108" pageNumber="387">Distribution.</emphasis>
E Guatemala, El Salvador, and S Honduras.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="109" lastPageNumber="388" pageId="108" pageNumber="387" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="108.[1460,2664,3371,3478]" lastBlockId="109.[131,1339,297,649]" lastPageId="109" lastPageNumber="388" pageId="108" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1460,1708,3449,3478]" pageId="108" pageNumber="387">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
No information is yet available. The Salvadorean Deermouse is presumably is similar to the Mexican Deermouse (PF. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[832,970,297,330]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="109" pageNumber="388" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">mexicanus</taxonomicName>
), especially the subspecies formerly referred to as P. m. saxitilis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
